# Seller Performance v1.0 — CANONICAL FREEZE

**STATUS: CANONICAL | FROZEN | NO AI**

The Seller Performance Reputation Engine v1.0 is frozen after QA approval.

## Frozen surfaces

- **Account summary card** (`/account`) — `data-ac-seller-performance="v1.0-frozen"`
- **Seller dashboard** (`/seller/performance`) — `data-seller-performance-dashboard="v1.0-frozen"`
- **Scoring formula** — `lib/seller-performance/master-spec.ts` weights and levels
- **Public API boundary** — `GET /api/seller/performance/[userId]` buyer-safe fields only

## Allowed changes

- Deterministic engine bug fixes (event queue, recalculation, anti-fraud)
- Broken navigation or data-loading fixes
- Accessibility and performance fixes that do not alter approved layout
- Super-admin audit tooling (does not change buyer-visible surfaces)

## Prohibited without explicit approval

- Structural UI redesign of summary card or dashboard
- Scoring formula / weight changes
- AI, ML, or estimated values
- Exposing internal score, formula, audit, or factor breakdown on public buyer surfaces
- Client-side score calculation in React components

## SSOT

- Engine: `lib/seller-performance/`
- Account summary: `lib/account-center/seller-performance-summary.ts`
- Freeze tests: `tests/seller-performance-freeze.test.ts`

If a change alters frozen layout or public API boundaries, **STOP and request explicit approval**.
